<chapter id="Chapter574636">
  <title>CRM Module</title>
  <para>The CRM Module organizes all of your contacts in one central location.
  This ideal setup eliminates the need for duplicate entries when an account
  has multiple classifications (i.e., a customer who is also a vendor) or when
  a contact is associated with more than one entity.</para>
  <para>Initially, you categorize Accounts as either an Organization or
  Individual. Then identify the Accounts as a Customer or Prospect, and
  further define them as a Vendor, Partner and/or Competitor as needed.
  Additional functionality is available when various classifications are
  selected.</para>
  <para>From CRM you can Manage Incidents, Create To-Do's, Monitor Projects
  and Track Opportunities. You have the ability to create stand alone To-Do's
  or associate To-Do's with Incidents and Opportunities.</para>
  <para>The following topics will be covered in this chapter:<itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
        <para>Universal Address Book</para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>Accounts</para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>Contacts</para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>Incident Management</para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>To-Do List Management</para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>Project Management</para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>Opportunity Management</para>
      </listitem>
    </itemizedlist></para>
